.:: Puzzle 4x4-Level-1-2::.
City: rome, boston, new-york, berlin
The people have 4 different jobs:  librarian, scientist, police-officer, writer
There are 4 different nationalities: polish, german, brazilian, egyptian
The people grow 4 different varities of flowers: begonia, iris, tulip, dahlia
1. the librarian is on the far right##1
2. the egyptian is the person who growsbegonia##1
3. the police-officer is on the right of the person traveling to rome##1
4. the person who growstulip is on the left of the scientist##1
5. the egyptian is on the left of the polish##1
6. the person traveling to new-york is the brazilian##1
7. the german is on the left of the person traveling to boston##1
8. the person who growstulip is on the left of the person traveling to rome##1
9. the person who growsbegonia is on the right of the person who growsdahlia##1

.:: Answer ::.
|               |     1      |     2      |    3     |     4      |
| City      | new-york     | rome       | boston | berlin        |
| Job          | writer     | scientist       | police-officer   | librarian   |
| Nationality   | brazilian      | german       | egyptian     | polish    |
| Flower         | tulip | dahlia | begonia | iris |

